<p>I am getting confused with pointers. Here is a code to swap two names. Please see the code. Consider Input : hellohai(for d) and asd(for e). Output i am getting : asd      1ellohai        1ellohai</p>  <pre><code>#include&lt;stdio.h&gt; #include&lt;stdlib.h&gt;  int main() {         char *d,*e,*f;           d=(char*)malloc(10);         e=(char*)malloc(5);          scanf("%s",d);         scanf("%s",e);          f=d;         d=e;            e=f; //while printing e it prints the whole value contained in f (i.e.1ellohai). How? size of e is 5 only          f[0]='1'; // f is in read-only memory. So this should fail?         printf("%s \t %s \t %s \n",d,e,f);           return 0; } </code></pre>